      "score": 97,
      "action": "BUY",
      "entity": "THE BOEING COMPANY",
      "narrative": "# CORRUPTION BRIEF: Boeing Company (BA)\n**Date of Signal: May 6, 2026 | Amount: $32.9B+ | Score: 97/100**\n\n---\n\nBoeing received two NASA contracts totaling approximately $32.9 billion — $22.4B and $10.5B respectively — representing one of the largest dual aerospace government awards on record, awarded to a company with an established pattern of federal contracting dependency, having received over **$163 billion in federal contracts since 2000** according to USASpending.gov data. Boeing's lobbying expenditures exceeded **$15 million annually** in recent congressional cycles, with documented contributions to members sitting on the Senate Commerce Committee and House Armed Services Committee, both bodies with direct oversight authority over NASA appropriations and aerospace procurement. Federal procurement records show Boeing has faced **19 contracting disputes, cost overruns, and Inspector General findings** related to NASA and DoD contracts since 2010, including the Space Launch System program which ran **$6 billion over budget** per NASA's own OIG reports. The pattern — large contract award following active lobbying cycles — mirrors documented sequences in 2014 (KC-46 tanker), 2016 (Air Force One), and 2020 (SLS), each of which subsequently triggered congressional or IG review.\n\n---\n\n**Sources:** USASpending.gov | NASA OIG | OpenSecrets.org | ProPublica Nonprofit Explorer\n*This brief contains documented facts. No forward-looking speculation implied.*"
